From 0c6a325618c7ce72ed3d8084676f65498a18630d Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Dong Chenchen <superdcc97@163.com>
Date: Mon, 27 Apr 2026 11:25:13 +0800
Subject: [PATCH 5/5] mm: fix self-deadlock in vma_prepare() with i_mmap lock
 batching

When execve batching is enabled (i_mmap_batching), vma_link_file()
caches the i_mmap_rwsem write lock across consecutive mmap calls
to avoid repeated lock acquire/release for the same mapping.

However, vma_prepare() calls i_mmap_lock_write_promote() which
tries to acquire i_mmap_rwsem for write. If the same mm already
holds a cached write lock on the same mapping (from the batching
path), this results in a recursive rwsem acquisition attempt,
causing a self-deadlock. This manifests as init hanging during
boot when mapping file-backed VMAs.

Fix by flushing any cached i_mmap lock before calling
i_mmap_lock_write_promote() in vma_prepare().

Fixes: fdbf18d326f2 ("mm: defer i_mmap insertion to batch across consecutive mmap calls")
Signed-off-by: OpenCode Agent <agent@opencodex.ai>
---
 mm/vma.c | 7 +++++++
 1 file changed, 7 insertions(+)

diff --git a/mm/vma.c b/mm/vma.c
index 79aa56705bc6..6ceb7cd7dba3 100644
--- a/mm/vma.c
+++ b/mm/vma.c
@@ -322,6 +322,13 @@ static void vma_prepare(struct vma_prepare *vp)
 			uprobe_munmap(vp->adj_next, vp->adj_next->vm_start,
 				      vp->adj_next->vm_end);
 
+		/*
+		 * If a previous vma_link_file() cached the i_mmap lock (e.g.
+		 * during exec batching), flush it now to avoid recursively
+		 * acquiring the same i_mmap_rwsem write lock.
+		 */
+		if (vp->vma->vm_mm->i_mmap_cached_mapping)
+			vma_link_file_flush(vp->vma->vm_mm);
 		i_mmap_lock_write_promote(vp->mapping);
 		if (vp->insert && vp->insert->vm_file) {
 			/*
